---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="Learn">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Learn</h1>
  <p class="text-ink-muted max-w-2xl mb-10">
    ISO 24229 is the international standard for written language conversion systems. Start here if you're new.
  </p>

  <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
    <Card href="/learn/what-is-iso-24229" title="What is ISO 24229?" body="How the standard works and what a code means." />
    <Card href="/learn/code-structure" title="Anatomy of a code" body="Four colon-separated segments: titular · source · target · identifying." />
    <Card href="/learn/examples" title="Worked examples" body="Real systems decoded, segment by segment." />
    <Card href="/learn/use-cases" title="Use cases" body="Where written language conversion shows up." />
    <Card href="/learn/glossary" title="Glossary" body="Defined terms from §3 of the standard." />
    <Card href="/learn/comparison" title="Comparison" body="How ISO 24229 relates to BCP 47, ALA-LC, ICAO, UN systems." />
    <Card href="/faq" title="FAQ" body="Common questions, briefly answered." />
    <Card href="/specification" title="Specification" body="Annex A Terms of Reference and ISO 19135 compliance." />
  </div>
</Layout>
